\section{Assessment}
We will test our project by setting up different configurations and making sure that the robot is able to classify the objects consistently. Success to us would mean that all objects placed on the surface should be placed in their corresponding target locations after correctly locating them. I think that the goals we have proposed here are realistic and intuitively straightforward to understand, however complications could arise when we integrate the code and hardware, so we will use our back-up approaches if necessary. Some reach goals that we have is to add complexity to the objects we are able to detect (ie: cell phone, cups, pencils, wires). 

